 additional mechanisms unix also popularized hierarchical file system with arbitrarily nested subdirectories originally introduced by multics other common operating systems era had ways divide storage device into multiple directories sections but they had fixed number levels often only one level several major proprietary operating systems eventually added recursive subdirectory capabilities also patterned after multics dec's rsx-11m's group user hierarchy evolved into vms directories cp/m's volumes evolved into ms-dos 20+ subdirectories hp's mpe groupaccount hierarchy ibm's ssp os/400 library systems were folded into broader posix file systems making command interpreter ordinary user-level program with additional commands provided separate programs was another multics innovation popularized by unix unix shell used same language for interactive commands for scripting shell scripts – there was no separate job control language like ibm's jcl since shell os commands were just another program user could choose even write his own shell new commands could be added without changing shell itself unix's innovative command-line syntax for creating modular chains producer-consumer processes pipelines made powerful programming paradigm coroutines widely available many later command-line interpreters have been inspired by unix shell fundamental simplifying assumption unix was its focus on newline- delimited text for nearly all file formats there were no binary editors original version unix – entire system was configured using textual shell command scripts common denominator i/o system was byte – unlike record-based file systems focus on text for representing nearly everything made unix pipes especially useful encouraged development simple general tools that could be easily combined perform more complicated ad hoc tasks focus on text bytes made system far more scalable portable than other systems over time text-based applications have also proven popular application areas such printing languages postscript odf at application layer internet protocols eg ftp smtp http soap sip unix popularized syntax for regular expressions that found widespread use unix programming interface became basis for widely implemented operating system interface standard posix see above c programming language soon spread beyond unix now ubiquitous systems applications programming early unix developers were important bringing concepts modularity reusability into software engineering practice spawning software tools movement over time leading developers unix programs that ran on established set cultural norms for developing software norms which became important influential technology unix itself this has been termed unix philosophy tcp/ip networking protocols were quickly implemented on unix versions widely used on relatively inexpensive computers which contributed internet explosion worldwide real-time connectivity which formed basis for implementations on many other platforms unix policy extensive on-line documentation for many years ready access all system source code raised programmer expectations contributed launch free software movement free unix unix-like variants see also operating system § unix unix-like operating systems console screenshots debian top popular linux distribution freebsd bottom popular unix-like operating system richard stallman announced gnu project ambitious effort create free software unix-like system free sense that everyone who received copy would be free use study modify redistribute gnu project's own kernel development project gnu hurd had not produced working kernel but linus torvalds released linux kernel free software under gnu general public license addition their use linux operating system many gnu packages – such gnu compiler collection rest gnu toolchain gnu c library gnu core utilities – have gone on play central roles other free unix systems well linux distributions consisting linux kernel large collections compatible software ha